r%20later%2C%20Keay%20moved%20to%20Alabama%20with%20her%2C%20and%20he%20enlisted%20in%20the%20US%20Army%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%2010%20years%2C%20Keay%20was%20stationed%20in%20various%20states%20in%20the%20US%20and%20he%20obtained%20his%20US%20citizenship%2C%20he%20said.%20Then%2C%20in%202002%2C%20he%20was%20assigned%20to%20outposts%20in%20Germany%20and%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Keay%20retired%20from%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20he%20said%20he%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20US.%20Meanwhile%2C%20he%20and%20his%20first%20wife%20divorced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Keay%20visited%20Yongsan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20a%20district%20in%20Seoul%2C%20where%20he%20met%20his%20current%20wife%20Mi%20ok%20Jeon.%20While%20they%20initially%20lived%20in%20Germany%2C%20Mi%20ok%20had%20difficulty%20adjusting%20to%20life%20in%20Waurichen%2C%20a%20small%20village%20near%20Germany's%20border%20with%20Belgium%20and%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20he%20said.%20Additionally%2C%20her%20son%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20had%20a%20child%20and%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20her%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f1bf490-9c05-44a2-970a-14461a5ea37c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20in%20South%20Korea%20is%20convenient%20and%20efficient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Keay%20sold%20the%20home%20he%20bought%20in%20Waurichen%20in%202005%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20moved%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.livingindaejeon.or.kr%2Fenglish%2Fintroduction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDaejeon%2C%20the%20fifth-biggest%20city%20in%20South%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20shows%20Daejeon%2C%20South%20Korea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ce01c543b5e59d16b59b14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKeay%20and%20his%20wife%20Mi%20ok%20rent%20an%20apartment%20in%20a%20complex%