20in%20job%20creation%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fhigh-wage-metro-areas-are-experiencing-sluggish-growth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20analysis%20from%20the%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20many%20remote%20workers%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20the%20South%2C%20workers%20in%20more%20blue-collar%20occupations%20may%20not%20benefit%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20COVID%20taught%20us%20anything%2C%20it's%20that%20remote%20work%20is%20a%20privilege%20only%20certain%20workers%20are%20able%20to%20enjoy.%20Our%20index%20focuses%20on%20policies%20that%20would%20most%20benefit%20low-wage%20workers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20do%20not%20receive%20employer%20benefits%20such%20as%20paid%20sick%20or%20family%20leave%20%E2%80%93%20much%20less%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20remotely%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Kaitlyn%20Henderson%2C%20report%20author%20and%20senior%20researcher%20at%20Oxfam%20America%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVKHSU%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20most%20worker-friendly%20states%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Oxfam%20report%20looks%20at%20three%20dimensions%20of%20what%20makes%20a%20state%20worker-friendly%3A%20Wages%2C%20worker%20protections%2C%20and%20the%20right%20to%20organize.%20Wages%20are%20weighted%20the%20most%20out%20of%20those%20three%20categories%3B%20key%20policies%20tracked%20in%20that%20dimension%20include%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20state%20minimum%20wage%20to%20the%20wage%20needed%20to%20sustain%20a%20household%20of%20four%2C%20that%20same%20ratio%20for%20unemployment%20payments%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20state%20lets%20its%20localities%20have%20control%20over%20raising%20their%20minimum%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorker%20protection%20makes%20up%2035%25%20of%20the%20score%3B%20key%20policies%20factored%20into%20the%20ranking%20include%20equal%20pay%20mandates%20targeting%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%2C%20paid%20sick%20and%20family%20leave%2C%20child%20labor%20protections%2C%20limiting%20quotas%20for%20warehouse%20workers%2C%20and%20heat%20safety%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20finally%2C%20the%20right%20to%20organize%20makes%20up%2025%25%20of%20the%20total%20composite%20score.%20The%20key%20policies%20Oxfam%20tracks%20there%20include%20whether%20states%20have%20right-to-work%20laws%2C%20which%20allow%20workers%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20joining%20unions%20but%20still%20benefit%20from%20their%20contracts%2C%20whether%20teachers%20are%20able%20to%20organize%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20state%20has%20laws%20that%20protect%20workers%20from%20employer%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20organize%20has%20been%20particularly%20controversial%20in%20the%20South%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20Republican%20governors%20of%20Alabama%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20Tennessee%20have%20all%20passed%20laws%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falabamareflector.com%2F2024%2F04%2F24%2Falabama-house-oks-sanctions-for-companies-that-voluntarily-recognize-unions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estripping%20away%20state%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20companies%20that%20voluntarily%20recognize%20labor%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20governors%20of%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Mississippi%20joined%20the%20aforementioned%20states%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgovernor.alabama.gov%2Fnewsroom%2F2024%2F04%2Fgovernor-ivey-other-southern-governors-issue-joint-statement-in-opposition-to-united-auto-workers-uaws-unionization-campaign%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissuing%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20deriding%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers%20campaign%20to%20organize%20workers%20at%20car%20manufacturing%20plants%20across%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOxfam%20gave%20Texas%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20and%20Georgia%20a%20score%20of%20zero%20out%20of%20one%20hundred%20on%20rights%20to%20organize%2C%20while%20Tennessee%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20and%20Alabama%20earned%20a%20score%20of%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724925362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cf2d3c1aa2ac29ee34ec82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20flood%20of%20workers%20have%20moved%20south%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%20many%20southern%20states%20offer%20lower%20wages%20and%20fewer%20worker%20protections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CEliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-us-states-high-wages-salaries-worker-rights-california-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crisis-Hit%20Himachal%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20Ministers%20Defer%20Salaries%20For%202%20Months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHimachal%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%20Sukhvinder%20Singh%20Sukhu%20and%20his%20ministers%20will%20defer%20salaries%20and%20allowances%20for%20two%20months%20to%20help%20battle%20a%20financial%20crisis%20inflamed%20by%20devastating%20landslides%2C%20flash%20floods%2C%20and%20heavy%20rain%20in%20August%2C%20last%20year%20and%20this.%20He%20also%20called%20on%20all%20MLAs%20to%20take%20pay%20cuts%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hill%20state%20has%20been%20hit%20by%20a%20wave%20of%20flash%20floods%20and%20landslides%20over%20the%