%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftata-shelves-plans-for-ipo-of-media-unit-after-buying-out-temasek-124082900593_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftata-shelves-plans-for-ipo-of-media-unit-after-buying-out-temasek-124082900593_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Crime%2C%20Poverty%2C%20Fear%3A%20Great%20Britain%20Is%20Not%20So%20Great%20Anymore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fc1v35r68_london-homeless-_625x300_29_August_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20I%20visited%20my%20favourite%20cafe%20in%20South%20London%2C%20known%20for%20its%20Illy%20coffee%20beans%20that%20I%20relish.%20As%20I%20savoured%20my%20coffee%2C%20a%20young%20man%2C%20wearing%20a%20sleeveless%20hoodie%20and%20shorts%2C%20casually%20walked%20in.%20He%20was%20carrying%20a%20hold-all%20bag%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20he%20had%20just%20come%20from%20the%20gym.%20But%20he%20had%20other%20plans.%20In%20the%20blink%20of%20an%20eye%2C%20he%20swept%20every%20last%20sandwich%20into%20his%20bag%20from%20a%20stocked%20shelf.%20As%20he%20walked%20past%20me%2C%20our%20eyes%20met.%20I%20thought%20about%20confronting%20him%20but%20instead%20took%20another%20sip%20of%20my%20coffee%20and%20pretended%20to%20be%20engrossed%20in%20my%20smartphone.%20The%20lone%20waiter%20and%20the%20manager%20behind%20the%20counter%20seemed%20helpless%20or%20perhaps%20paralysed%20with%20fear.%20The%20boy%20walked%20out%20as%20if%20he%20had%20come%20in%20for%20his%20daily%20grocery%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20turned%20to%20the%20manager%2C%20still%20tucked%20safely%20behind%20his%20counter%2C%20and%20asked%20whether%20he%20would%20report%20the%20incident%20to%20the%20police.%20Still%20shaken%2C%20he%20gave%20me%20a%20weary%20smile%20and%20said%20there%20was%20no%20point%20calling%20the%20police.%20He%20explained%20that%20shoplifting%20under%20%C2%A3200%20was%20not%20worth%20reporting.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%202014%20law%20had%20categorised%20shoplifting%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Blow-value%26quot%3B%20crime%2C%20inviting%20minimal%20or%20no%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELondon%20is%20a%20paradise%20for%20shoplifters.%20But%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20Shoplifting%20cases%20are%20spiralling%20out%20of%20control%20across%20the%20UK.%20According%20to%20the%20Office%20for%20National%20Statistics%2C%20last%20year%20was%20the%20worst%20on%20record%20for%20shoplifting%2C%20with%20police%20recording%204%2C30%2C000%20offences.%20The%20retailers'%20body%2C%20the%20British%20Retail%20Consortium%2C%20says%20these%20figures%20are%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20actual%20incidents%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20not%20reported%20for%20fear%20of%20violence.%20The%20body%20believes%20the%20cases%20crossed%208%20million%20last%20year%2C%20with%20retailers%20losing%20over%20%C2%A31.8%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Broken%20Britain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar-right%20politicians%20claim%2C%20without%20much%20evidence%2C%20that%20shoplifting%20is%20a%20pastime%20of%20'illegal'%20immigrants.%20That%20they%20exist%20outside%20the%20system%20and%20therefore%20escape%20scrutiny.%20These%20politicians%20lament%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20country's%20resources%20are%20being%20overwhelmed%20as%20huge%20amounts%20of%20money%20are%20being%20spent%20on%20housing%20and%20feeding%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20human%20rights%20activists%20and%20community%20workers%20believe%20the%20alarming%20rise%20in%20shoplifting%20is%20linked%20to%20a%20grave%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis.%20Brexit%20and%20then%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20led%20to%20an%20upswing%20in%20unemployment%20and%20pushed%20scores%20of%20communities%20below%20the%20poverty%20line.%20There%20are%20numerous%20reports%20that%20claim%20that%20much%20of%20Britain's%20woes%20are%20due%20to%20its%20breaking%20free%20from%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20its%20inability%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20devastating%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BWe%20Haven't%20Got%20Food%20Tonight.%20Can%20You%20Help%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoverty%20has%20affected%20many%20deprived%20communities%20and%20pushed%20them%20into%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20have%20become%20dependent%20on%20food%20charities.%20A%20recent%20report%20by%20Bristol%20University%20cited%20a%20pupil's%20letter%20to%20his%20school%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20got%20any%20food%20tonight.%20Please%20can%20you%20help%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20university%20research%2C%20focusing%20on%20food%20charity%20in%20schools%2C%20revealed%20that%20there%20are%20over%204%2C000%20school-based%20food%20banks%20in%20primary%20and%20secondary%20schools%20across%20England.%20This%20is%20in%20addition%20to%20various%20charities%20-%20including%20some%20run%20by%20Indian%20Sikhs%20-%20that%20run%20food%20banks%20both%20in%20schools%20and%20at%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreat%20Britain%20is%20manifestly%20becoming%20poorer.%20Even%20for%20a%20casual%20visitor%20to%20the%20country%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20miss%20its%20bloated%20underbelly.%20Many%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20White%20colleague%20visiting%20Mumbai%20from%20London%20was%20shocked%20to%20see%20scores%20of%20homeless%20people%20sleeping%20under%20flyovers%20and%20on%20footpaths.%20She%20told%20me%20she%20was%20genuinely%20moved%20by%20the%20squalor.%20London's%20homeless%20may%20be%20fewer%20in%20number%20than%20India's%2C%20but%20they%20are%20ubiquitous.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Deeply%20Unequal%20Society%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20is%20visible%20everywhere.%20Wherever%20you%20go%20in%20London%20-%20or%20even%20other%20big%20cities%20in%20Britain%20-%20you%20cannot%20miss%20homeless%20people%20along%20the%20high%20streets%20and%20open%20public%20spaces.%20They%20sleep%20or%20rest%20in%20beds%20made%20of%20cardboard%20and%20tattered%20blankets.%20They%20take%20refuge%20under%20railway%20bridges%20and%20public%20parks%2C%20where%20benches%20serve%20as%20their%20beds.%20They%20look%20fatigued%20and%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20wealth%2C%20London%20has%20pockets%20of%20severe%20poverty%20and%20deprivation.%20Child%20poverty%20rates%20are%20higher%20in%20London%20than%20in%20any%20other%20English%20region.%20London's%20crime%20rates%20are%20higher%20than%20any%20other%20major%20European%20cities%2C%20with%20rising%20concerns%20about%20knife%20attacks%2C%20gang%20violence%20and%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeneath%20London's%20gleaming%20surface%20lies%20social%20inequalities%2C%20economic%20woes%2C%20and%20extreme%20poverty%20that%20form%20the%20city's%20dark%20netherworld.%20The%20wealth%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%20is%20staggering%2C%20with%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20earners%20holding%2030%25%20of%20the%20city's%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistorical%20perspective%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20wasn't%20always%20like%20this%2C%20London%2C%20and%20much%20of%20England%2C%20has%20been%20through%20a%20cycle%20of%20decay%20and%20regeneration.%20A%20very%20impressionable%20young%20Trinidadian%20writer%2C%20CLR%20James%2C%20visited%20England%20in%201932.%20His%20portrayal%20of%20London%20in%20the%201930s%20in%20Letter%20from%20London%20could%20be%20true%20of%20today's%20time%20as%20well.%20%26quot%3BI%20saw%20London%20with%20new%20eyes%3B%20I%20saw%20the%20vast%20multitudes%20toiling%20to%20make%20a%20few%20wealthy%3B%20I%20saw%20the%20rich%20with%20their%20money%2C%20their%20resources%2C%20their%20million%20servants%2C%20exploiting%20the%20great%2C%20blind%2C%20unconscious%20masses%20of%20the%20poor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20observed%20in%20one%20of%20his%20essays.%20In%20another%20place%2C%20he%20captured%20his%20uneasy%20feeling%20thus%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20both%20a%20stranger%20and%20a%20prisoner%2C%20trapped%20in%20a%20society%20that%20is%20indifferent%20to%20the%20suffering%20of%20the%20majority%20and%20obsessed%20with%20its%20own%20decline.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20too%2C%20much%20like%20in%20the%201930s%2C%20many%20here%20have%20started%20complaining%20that%20Britain%20is%20broken.%20Its%20economy%20is%20stagnating%2C%20its%20politics%20is%20divisive%2C%20and%20its%20society%20is%20in%20disarray.%20Actually%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer%20has%20been%20saying%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20the%20UK's%20%26quot%3Beconomy%20is%20broken%2C%20the%20health%20service%20is%20broken%2C%20and%20public%20service%20is%20broken%26quot%3B.%20His%20Labour%20Party%20was%20voted%20to%20power%20in%20the%20July%20election%20on%20its%20promise%20of%20fixing%20a%20%26quot%3Bbroken%20Britain%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20Is%20Marching%20Ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20true%20that%20the%20British%20economy%20has%20been%20stagnating%20for%20years.%20But%20the%20country%20was%20far%20ahead%20of%20India%20in%202014%2C%20which%20was%20the%20world's%2010th%20biggest%20economy%20at%20the%20time.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20however%2C%20India%20grew%20steadily.%20In%202021%2C%20it%20left%20the%20UK%20behind%20and%20became%20the%20fifth-largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world.%20The%20Indian%20government's%20economic%20policies%20stand%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20lacklustre%20vision%20of%20successive%20British%20governments%20over%2015%20years.%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20government%20ensured%20that%20India%20had%20political%20and%20economic%20stability%20and%20continuity.%20Britain%20was%20not%20that%20lucky%2C%20seeing%20six%20different%20governments%20led%20by%20six%20different%20prime%20ministers%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20voted%20to%20power%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer%20said%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20mess%20to%20fix%26quot%3B%2C%20blaming%20the%20outgoing%20Tory%20government%20that%20had%20been%20in%20power%20from%202010%20to%202024%20for%20leading%20the%20country%20here.%20As%20historian%20Niall%20Ferguson%20notes%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20UK's%20decline%20is%20a%20long-term%20process%2C%20driven%20by%20a%20combination%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20economic%20mismanagement%2C%20social%20inequality%2C%20and%20political%20polarisation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20first%20step%20towards%20%26quot%3Bfixing%20the%20mess%26quot%3B%2C%20Starmer%20has%20proposed%20to%20raise%20taxes.%20But%20that%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20betrayal%20because%20the%20party%20had%20promised%20not%20to%20increase%20taxation.%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20even%20warned%20that%20the%20forthcoming%20budget%20is%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20be%20painful%26quot%3B.%20It%20will%20get%20worse%2C%20he%20said%2C%20before%20it%20gets%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20debate%20rages%20on%20in%20the%20media%2C%20Starmer%20quietly%20set%20out%20on%20an%20official%20trip%20to%20Germany%20and%20France%20to%20%26quot%3Breset%26quot%3B%20Britain's%20relations%20with%20Europe.%C2%A0If%20all%20goes%20well%2C%20this%20reset%20might%20help%20Britain%20steady%20the%20post-Brexit%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724922600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fidmk7ajg_london-homeless-_625x300_29_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcrime-poverty-fear-great-britain-is-not-so-great-anymore-6443707%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brexit%20a